	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=143701><span id= >Raymon</span></a><br><span id=notbold>53 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This is the rough strategy to fighting MM since no one ever manages to post these things...<br><br>Position your raid in the far corner across from MM, <br><br>Have a monk pull MM's guards (wrulons) to the raid one by one and kill them FAST. Once they are down...pull MM over to one of the corners near the entrance to his chamber, where the raid should be. Corner MM, have mages and shamans spam pets, and monks DP to push him in to the corner against the tank. Once the tank has good aggro, add your DPS. Have druids SotW, have bards play AE resists near the MA. Keep a good CCH on your tank and wear him down. Watch for rage, collect your loot. <br><br><br>Important...you will get repops during the fight so have an off-tank or mezzer ready, no one in the raid can wander away from the wall. Doing so will wipe the raid. <br><br>PP pops in the middle of the room, clear the guards to the PP, hail it...etc etc. <br><br>And that, is how it's done...</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Raymon Stoutheart<br>61st season High Priest of Brell Serilis</td></tr>
